=== Surveillance allegations ===
In December 2020, ''[[The Guardian]]'' reported that a security researcher identified evidence of surveillance campaign against Americans by China Unicom via Caribbean mobile networks. China Unicom strongly denied the allegations.<ref>{{Cite news|last=Kirchgaessner|first=Stephanie|date=2020-12-15|title=China suspected of spying on Americans via Caribbean phone networks|language=en-GB|work=[[The Guardian]]|url=https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2020/dec/15/revealed-china-suspected-of-spying-on-americans-via-caribbean-phone-networks|url-status=live|access-date=2020-12-16|issn=0261-3077|archive-date=2020-12-15|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201215233406/https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2020/dec/15/revealed-china-suspected-of-spying-on-americans-via-caribbean-phone-networks}}</ref>

